Pakistan Stocks: Pakistan Airlines, Pakistan Refinery, Engro

-- B y   K h u r r u m   A n i s
-- 
2011-02-14T12:17:48Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-14/pakistan-stocks-pakistan-airlines-pakistan-refinery-engro.html
  Pakistan ’s key Karachi Stock
Exchange 100 index rose 2.75, or 0.02 percent, to 11,946.09.    Pakistan International Airlines Corp . (PIAA PA) surged the
most in almost eight months in Karachi trading after workers
ended a four-day strike on Feb. 11.  The national flag carrier jumped 14.8 percent to 2.87
rupees, the most since June 17.  Pakistan International’s Chief Executive Officer Aijaz Haroon resigned, paving the way for the carrier to resume
flights, Pakistan Defense Minister Mukhtar Ahmed said at a
televised press conference in Islamabad Feb. 11. The strike had
left more than 50,000 passengers stranded and 250 planes stuck
at various airports in the country, according to Mashood Tajwar,
a company spokesman.    Pakistan Refinery Ltd . (PRL PA) rose 2.7 percent to 103.06
rupees after the nation’s second-largest oil processor posted a
profit in the second quarter, compared with a loss a year
earlier.  The company reported net income of 905.1 million rupees
($10.6 million) in the three months ended Dec. 31, compared with
a 1.03 billion rupee loss, according to a filing to the stock
exchange today.  Engro Corp. (ENGRO PA), a maker of fertilizer, dairy
products and plastics, gained 2.2 percent to 214.64 rupees after
full-year profit rose 73 percent on higher sales.  Net income rose to 6.44 billion rupees, or 20.72 rupees a
share, in the 12 months ended Dec. 31, from 3.72 billion rupees,
or 12.24 rupees a share a year ago, the Karachi-based company
said in a statement to the stock exchange today. Sales rose to
79.9 billion rupees from 58.2 billion.  To contact the reporter on this story:
